news.title: Delhi LG directs DDA to extend single-window special camps for PM-UDAY till March 2025
news.para: During these eight days, 1,152 conveyance deeds/authorisation slips were issued, and 283 properties were registered by the sub-registrars, providing final ownership rights to the property holders, the statement added.

news.title: Over 41 lakh people in Uttar Pradesh to benefit from Pradhan Mantri SVAMITVA Yojana
news.para: To note, SVAMITVA is a scheme of the Ministry of Panchayati Raj that provides a ‘Record of Rights' to village household owners.

news.title: Chennai development body to e-auction plots along Outer Ring Road in January
news.para: CMDA aims to develop CORR into a vibrant economic corridor featuring premium housing, industries, warehousing, hotels and urban forests, with areas such as Minjur, Red Hills, Poonamallee, and Vandalur integrated with the third master plan.

news.title: Greater Noida: GNIDA files FIR against 18 people over illegal housing projects in Tusyana
news.para: These projects encroached on govt land, caused revenue loss to the govt, and deceived customers by offering plots and flats at cheaper rates.

news.title: Maharashtra looks to boost builders' participation in e-registration process for first sale flats
news.para: The initiative aimed at reducing footfall at registration offices by enabling the buyers to complete the online registration process from the developers' offices in coordination with the property registration department.

news.title: Facebook renews lease for 3.7 lakh sq ft office in Hyderabad's Hitec City
news.para: Meta has renewed its lease for 367,000 sq ft office space in Hyderabad for five more years, with a total rental payout of over Rs 170 crore. This commitment highlights the city's robust commercial real estate market and its importance as a tech hub in India.

news.title: Sri Lotus Developers files DRHP for Rs 792-crore IPO
news.para: As per the draft papers filed on Tuesday, proceeds from the fresh issue to the extent of Rs 550 crore will be used for investment in its subsidiaries for part-funding the development and construction cost of its ongoing projects.

news.title: UP entity illegally using out tradename, ED action not linked to us: Kalpataru Group
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate had on December 19 issued a statement to say that it seized Rs 1.02 crore in cash after it conducted searches at multiple locations in Uttar Pradesh in an alleged Ponzi scheme linked money laundering case against "Kalpataru Group of companies."

news.title: 2024 round-up: Indian real estate continues to attract robust institutional inflows
news.para: After witnessing subdued activity in the previous few quarters, investments in office segment surged significantly in the third quarter predominantly driven by foreign investors.

news.title: Ayodhya administration demolish houses on Saptsaagar land
news.para: There are more than a dozen mythological ponds in Ayodhya mentioned in various religious texts but have vanished in the due course of time after being encroached upon and sold by land sharks.

news.title: Chennai metro rail to begin land acquisition for Coimbatore metro project
news.para: M A Siddique, managing director, CMRL, said they were hopeful that the Union govt would approve the metro rail projects in Coimbatore and Madurai soon.

news.title: Doctor duped of Rs 70 lakh in flat purchase deal in Navi Mumbai
news.para: The accused showed a flat located in Roadpali area of Kalamboli to the doctor and expressed their intention to sell it to him despite the fact that it had been already sold to someone else.

news.title: Mumbai Metro One lenders in talks to sell Rs 1,226-crore debt to NARCL
news.para: The National Asset Reconstruction Company (NARCL) has offered ₹1,063 crore to acquire Mumbai Metro One (MMOPL)'s principal outstanding debt of ₹1,226 crore, the people said.

news.title: Pune: Collectorate gets advanced system to track illegal sand mining
news.para: The pilot project, launched last month, enables real-time monitoring of sand-mining activities across 200 locations throughout the district. The office features an advanced surveillance system that includes GPS tracking of vehicles involved in sand transportation.

news.title: Odisha govt asks civic bodies to invite applications for PM housing scheme for urban areas
news.para: Odisha Urban Housing Mission (OUHM) under the Housing & Urban Development Department has issued an instruction to the civic bodies to this effect.

news.title: PE investments in Indian real estate rise 10% to $4.3 billion in 2024: Savills India
news.para: Foreign institutional investors accounted for 88% of the total investment activity in 2024, reinforcing their dominant role in driving growth in the sector.

news.title: N Srinivasan, other promoters steps down from India Cements' board
news.para: The Aditya Birla Group firm has completed the acquisition of 10.13 crore equity shares of India Cements Ltd (ICL), representing 32.72 per cent of the equity share capital of the company.

news.title: Prime minister to launch 58 lakh property cards under SVAMITVA
news.para: SVAMITVA Scheme, which was launched in 2020, aims at providing a "Record of Rights" to every property owner in the Village Abadi area.

news.title: Deep Financial Consultants' director buys apartment for Rs 106 crore in Mumbai’s Worli
news.para: The newly purchased apartment is spread over a total of over 7,139 sq ft area in one of the wings of the tower Oberoi Three Sixty West on Dr Annie Besant Road and is on the 60th floor and 44th habitable floor.

news.title: Nearly 77% realization of recovery certificates issued by UP-RERA in Ghaziabad
news.para: According to data from the board of revenue, Ghaziabad has a 23% pendency rate, while GB Nagar has 72% and Varanasi has 94%.
